speech: In every outthrust headland, in every curving beach, in every grain of sand there is the story of the earth. Rachel Carson, Author of Silent Spring.
The sea, the great unifier, is man's only hope. Now, as never before, the old phrase has a literal meaning: we are all in the same boat. Jacques Cousteau, Oceanologist.
The clearest way into the Universe is through a forest wilderness. John Muir
